<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="39" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="39">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="39">
The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Massarinaceae" genus="Massarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Massarina" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Massarina</taxonomicName>
has been known as a phylogenetically diverse group in the order 
<taxonomicName genus="Pleosporales" lsidName="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" rank="genus">Pleosporales</taxonomicName>
based on molecular data (
<bibRefCitation author="Liew, ECY" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="31" pageNumber="56" pagination="803 - 813" title="An evaluation of the monophyly of Massarina based on ribosomal DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/15572536.2003.11833174" volume="94" year="2002">Liew et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and most members in 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Massarinaceae" genus="Massarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Massarina" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Massarina</taxonomicName>
except for the type species (
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. eburnea" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="eburnea">M. eburnea</taxonomicName>
) are morphologically variable. The taxon, 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Massarinaceae" genus="Massarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Massarina pandanicola" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pandanicola">Massarina pandanicola</taxonomicName>
collected from 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pandanus" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pandanus</taxonomicName>
sp. in Thailand is introduced here as a new species with both morphology and phylogeny support. The morphology of the taxon showed similar conidia with 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Massarinaceae" genus="Massarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Massarina eburnean" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="eburnean">Massarina eburnean</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tanaka, K" journalOrPublisher="Studies in mycology" pageId="35" pageNumber="60" pagination="75 - 136" title="Revision of the Massarineae (Pleosporales, Dothideomycetes)." url="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2015.10.002" volume="82" year="2015">Tanaka et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
), but based on phylogenetic analysis of combined ITS, LSU, SSU and TEF1 gene sequence data, the new taxon 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pandanicola" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="pandanicola">M. pandanicola</taxonomicName>
is well-separated from other species in 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Massarinaceae" genus="Massarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Massarina" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Massarina</taxonomicName>
(Figure 9) with high bootstrap support (79 % in ML). This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Massarinaceae" genus="Massarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Massarina" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Massarina</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pandanus" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pandanus</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
